        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: close readline interface and destroy read stream in transcript store",
        "body": "Related: #98467\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes a file descriptor leak: `createReadStream` + `readline.createInterface` were not cleaned up after `for await` loop exit.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nWrap the loop in `try/finally` that calls `lines.close()` and `stream.destroy()`.\n\n## User Impact\n\nNo user-visible change. Prevents file descriptor exhaustion when reading large transcripts.\n\n## Evidence\n\n```\nsrc/agents/tools/transcripts-tool.test.ts\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\n     Tests  10 passed (10)\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 20.13s\n```",
